Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Palace of Ramses III (Tell el-Maskhuta), From fill, apparently removed from casemate chambers within temple enclosure.
Curator's comments: cf. Petrie, Tanis I, 28 [Petrie notes that 35 fragments went to the BM, with a piece of charred beam; other fragments went to Bristol, Boston, Bolton, Geneva, York, Liverpool and the Charterhouse School] See Brissaud and Zivie-Coche - Tanis 1987-1997, (1998) p.159, 106 [pl.23]. Fleur Shearman and Stephen Quirke are working on associated fragments at the Petrie Museum.
